raining with `fp16`, AMP says that we need to provide a model with parameters located on CUDA. \r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nThe problem is reproduced in [this Kernel](https://www.kaggle.com/kashnitsky/distillbert-catalyst-amazon-product-reviews?scriptVersionId=22987225) (Version 3). \r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nExpect the model to train normally\r\n\r\n**Screenshots**\r\nCalling `runner.train` \r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://habrastorage.org/webt/fd/rp/0i/fdrp0i4u6uzxhyd5wjafuc1k3w0.png\" />\r\n\r\nGetting error:\r\n```\r\nWhen using amp.initialize, you need to provide a model with parameters\r\nlocated on a CUDA device before passing it no matter what optimization level\r\nyou chose. Use model.to('cuda') to use the default device.\r\n```\r\n<img src=\"https://habrastorage.org/webt/a1/im/vo/a1imvo0wsnv2vuddgdteglhu0ua.png\" />\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nThe problem is solved if I pass `model=model.cuda()` to `runner.train`. But I don't think it's designed to be done like that. \r\n\r\nCatalyst version is 19.11.","closed_by":{"login":"Yorko","id":3973673,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM5NzM2NzM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3973673?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Yorko","html_url":"https://github.com/Yorko","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Yorko/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Yorko/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Yorko/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Yorko/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Yorko/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Yorko/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Yorko/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Yorko/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Yorko/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catalyst-team/catalyst/issues/494/rea